ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, it is a class which teaches you how to think differently about measurement in nursing research and challenges you to employ this in a practical proposed study.

Yes, I will recommend this course to other students, as instruments are important part of our nursing research. Instruments are cheap ways to measure changes in outcomes that we intend to detect after implementing interventions in nursing research.

N903 is a course pertaining to measurement. I would recommend this course to another student because it is essential for students to have knowledge of measurement when designing research studies and to evaluate research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I go about reading research differently with a critical eye examining how measurement was addressed and whether additional measures need to be taken into account.

after this course, I have more understanding on the development of instruments, and choose of instruments, which helps a lot in choosing proper instruments to measure outcomes that my dissertation wants to detect.
Yes. The course helped me decide which measures would be most useful in my dissertation research.
